content.description:
Crimpy/Facey climb. Start on the black face and head up lightly on crimps. Do not go right and use the connecting boulder.

For the downclimb, suffer shuffle the chimney.
content.protection: A fall from the top sans pad would be injurious.
content.location: I believe this is the south west face of the southern boulder, after the crevice between the two main boulder piles.

content.description:
Start hanging on good holds and make powerful moves onto even higher jugs!

Walk or chimney down the back side of the boulder

Begin on the corner of this boulder with a left heel hook and right edge. Use good starting hand holds to eventually bump up to some (probably) sandy slopers/manageable side-crimps. Work your feet up then finish the top out.
content.location: Furthest line south and west of this boulder congregation.

content.description:
Fun slabby problem with big holds to start.  Start on the bottom with good feet and okay hands.  Work your way up anyway you choose to the top and you can downclimb the smooth face to the left of the top out.  Make sure your descent with your feet or the downclimb may be tricky, but then again if you can make it to the top you probably already have descent foot work ;-).  here's some beta if you want it

https://youtu.be/K1wvFVvIGHE
content.location: Located in this unknown pile.  It is directly across from the triangle boulder.  So you can go to the triangle boulder and look straight out from it and see this boulder close by.
